a_0.formal problem:
theorem
fixes n k :: nat
assumes h0 : "n = 22"
and h1 : "k = 19"
shows  "binomial n k = 1540"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 Compute $\dbinom{22}{19}$. The final Answer is 1540
 ### Proof
 \begin{align} \dbinom{22}{19} &= \dbinom{22}{3} \\ &= \dfrac{22!}{19!3!} \\ &= \dfrac{22\times 21\times 20}{3\times 2\times 1} \\ &= 22 \times \dfrac{21}{3} \times \dfrac{20}{2} \\ &= 22 \times 7 \times 10 \\
 &= \boxed{1540}. \end{align}
 *)

theorem
fixes n k :: nat
assumes h0 : "n = 22"
and h1 : "k = 19"
shows  "binomial n k = 1540"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer
a_0.informal problem: Find the binomial coefficient of n = 22 and k = 19. The final answer is 1540.
